---
title: Using AsciiMath
---

• Stencila Markdown also supports writing math using AsciiMath, a simpler syntax than TeX.

• [Add](type:0) display AsciiMath equations using a code block with ``asciimath`` as the language.

• You can also [add](type:1) inline AsciiMath within paragraphs.

***

The circumference of a circle is,

```asciimath
C = 2 pi r
```

***

where `r`{asciimath} is the radius of the circle.

